menu "PID Controller"

    config PID_CTRL_IQ_FORMAT
        int "IQmath Q-format (GLOBAL_IQ)"
        range 1 30
        default 24
        help
            Q-format used by the _iq backend. This value is applied as
            GLOBAL_IQ before including IQmathLib.h, so all _IQ() / _IQtoF()
            / _IQmpy() calls in pid_ctrl use this fractional bit count.

            Typical choices:
              - 24 (default): high precision, range approx. +/- 128.
              - 16         : more headroom, range approx. +/- 32768.
              - 8          : very large range, lower precision.

            If your application #defines GLOBAL_IQ itself before including
            pid_ctrl.h, that user definition wins and this option is ignored.

endmenu
